The bulk g-C3N4 was synthesized by one-step polymerization of melamine according to a procedure described in our previous paper [27]. In a typical process, the precursor melamine was thermally treated in a tube furnace at 550 C for 2 h with a heating rate of 5 Cmin 1 under N2 atmosphere. The obtained yellow-colored bulk g-C3N4 was collected and ground into powder for further use.
