The g-C3N4 nanosheets were obtained by liquid exfoliation of the as-synthesized bulk g-C3N4 in water. In detail, 0.1 g of bulk g-C3N4 powder was dispersed in 250 mL water and then ultrasonicated for about 15 h. The resulting suspension was centrifuged at about 5000 rpm to remove the residual unexfoliated g-C3N4 and then the supernatant suspension was heated at 100 C. The obtained pale yellow colored g-C3N4 nanosheets are named as CN.
